      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Human review remains because the blockers are contributor real behavior proof and maintainer acceptance of compatibility-sensitive success-response caps, not a narrow automated code repair.; Cleared: The diff adds no dependency, workflow, permission, credential, package, or supply-chain surface; the security-relevant availability hardening is tracked as merge risk. (sha=e5d41f83df59304a17876ad71373ed7faac675cb)",
      "review_summary": "The branch replaces unbounded OpenAI Batch status, ChatGPT OAuth token, and Realtime client-secret success-response reads with shared 16 MiB bounded response helpers.\n\nPR surface: Source +10. Total +10 across 3 files.\n\nReproducibility: Source-level yes, live changed-path no. Current main reaches raw `response.json()` and `arrayBuffer()` in the targeted OpenAI paths, and an oversized streaming response would exercise the unbounded buffering path, but I did not run live OpenAI endpoints.",
